[Revelation 19:7](../../../bib/kjv/rev019.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">rev 19:7</span></span>

wife

The "Lamb's wife" here is the "bride", ([Rev
21:9](../../../bib/kjv/rev021.htm#009).md), the Church, identified with the
"heavenly Jerusalem", ([Heb 12:22](../../../bib/kjv/heb012.htm#022).md);
([Heb 12:23](../../../bib/kjv/heb012.htm#023).md), and to be distinguished
from Israel, the adulterous and repudiated "wife" of Jehovah, yet to be
restored; ([Isa 54:1-10](../../../bib/kjv/isa054.htm#001).md); ([Hos
2:1-17](../../../bib/kjv/hos002.htm#001).md); who is identified with the
earth ([Hos 2:23](../../../bib/kjv/hos002.htm#023).md). A forgiven and
restored wife could not be called either a virgin ([Co2
11:2](../../../bib/kjv/co2011.htm#002).md); ([Co2
11:3](../../../bib/kjv/co2011.htm#003).md) or a bride.

[Revelation 19:8](../../../bib/kjv/rev019.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">rev 19:8</span></span>

righteousness

The garment is Scripture is a symbol of righteousness. In the bad
ethical sense, it symbolizes self-righteousness (for example, ([Isa
64:6](../../../bib/kjv/isa064.htm#006).md); ([Phi
3:6-8](../../../bib/kjv/phi003.htm#006).md) the best that a moral and
religious man under law could do). In the good ethical sense, the
garment symbolizes "the righteousness of God. . .upon all them that
believe."

(See Scofield) - ([Rom 3:21](../../../bib/kjv/rom003.htm#021).md).

[Revelation 19:11](../../../bib/kjv/rev019.htm#011.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_011">rev 19:11</span></span>

